In [[Singapore]], rumours that the [[Ministry of Manpower (Singapore)|Ministry of Manpower]] had declared a voluntary non-work day appeared on the evening of Thursday, September 24. 2015 as the [[Pollutant Standards Index]] (PSI) was 313-341 in the [[Hazardous]] range after 7pm-5am. The Ministry of Manpower lodged a police report over a hoax post on social media ([[WhatsApp]] or [[Facebook]]) that claimed it had declared a "voluntary non-work day" on Friday, September 25, 2015 as a result of the [[2015 Southeast Asian haze|haze]].<ref>{{cite web|title=MOM lodges police report over hoax post|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/mom-lodges-police-report-over-hoax-post|accessdate=29 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Haze & confused|url=http://news.asiaone.com/news/singapore/haze-confused|accessdate=29 September 2015}}</ref><ref name="tnp">{{cite web|title=MOM debunks fake 'voluntary non-work day' Facebook post|url=http://www.tnp.sg/news/singapore-news/mom-debunks-fake-voluntary-non-work-day-facebook-post}}</ref> - this [[Hoax]] is part of the [[Hoaxes in Singapore]].
